<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Press Kit | {{ site_name }}</title>
<meta name="description" content="Press kit for journalists, podcasters, and researchers covering the Pentagon's PURSUE UAP disclosure. Fact sheet, embed assets, verification manifest.">
<link rel="canonical" href="{{ site_url }}/press.html">

<link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles.css">
<style>
  .press-page{max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px 24px}
  .press-page h1{font-size:clamp(36px,5vw,56px);color:#fff;margin-bottom:14px}
  .press-page h2{color:#52b4ff;font-size:22px;margin:40px 0 12px;letter-spacing:.01em}
  .press-page p{color:#dfe6ef;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:14px}
  .fact-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(160px,1fr));gap:14px;margin:24px 0}
  .fact-tile{background:rgba(82,180,255,.04);border:1px solid rgba(82,180,255,.15);padding:18px;border-radius:8px;text-align:center}
  .fact-tile .n{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:24px;color:#52b4ff;font-weight:700}
  .fact-tile .l{font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.5px;color:#7a92b0;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:4px}
  pre{background:rgba(0,0,0,.4);border:1px solid rgba(82,180,255,.15);padding:18px;border-radius:6px;overflow-x:auto;color:#52b4ff;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:12px;line-height:1.5}
  ul{color:#dfe6ef;margin-left:24px;line-height:1.8}
  a{color:#52b4ff}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="starfield"></div><div class="grid-bg"></div>

<main class="press-page">
  <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:2px;color:#52b4ff;margin-bottom:16px"><a href="../index.html" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none">← PURSUE Index</a></p>
  <h1>Press Kit</h1>
  <p>An independent index of the U.S. Department of War's PURSUE (Presidential Unsealings and Reporting System for UAP Encounters) disclosure. Free to cite, free to embed, free to verify.</p>

  <h2>Fact sheet</h2>
  <div class="fact-grid">
    <div class="fact-tile"><div class="n">{{ total }}</div><div class="l">Total Files</div></div>
    {% for agency, n in by_agency.items() %}
    <div class="fact-tile"><div class="n">{{ n }}</div><div class="l">{{ agency }}</div></div>
    {% endfor %}
    <div class="fact-tile"><div class="n">{{ high_anomaly | length }}</div><div class="l">High Anomaly (≥80)</div></div>
  </div>

  <h2>What we are</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>An independent mirror and index of public-domain U.S. government files released via war.gov/UFO.</li>
    <li>Not affiliated with the Department of War, the FBI, NASA, or any U.S. government entity.</li>
    <li>Every file links to its original source URL and includes a SHA-256 hash.</li>
    <li>The Anomalousness Index is our editorial scoring of evidentiary weight, with transparent methodology. Not a probability of extraterrestrial origin.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Use of materials</h2>
  <p>All underlying files are works of the U.S. Government and are in the public domain (17 U.S.C. § 105). You may cite, embed, screenshot, and republish freely. Attribution to the original federal agency is courteous; attribution to this index is appreciated but not required.</p>

  <h2>Embed code</h2>
  <p>Embed any individual file's player into your story:</p>
<pre>&lt;iframe src="{{ site_url }}/files/&lt;file-id&gt;.html"
        width="100%" height="720"
        style="border:0;border-radius:8px"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</pre>

  <h2>Verification manifest</h2>
  <p>Download the SHA-256 manifest of every file we mirror, and confirm hash equality against the original war.gov source:</p>
  <p><a href="verification-manifest.json" download>verification-manifest.json</a></p>

  <h2>API</h2>
  <p>Public read-only JSON endpoints:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="api/files.json">{{ site_url }}/api/files.json</a> &mdash; index of all files</li>
    <li><code>{{ site_url }}/api/files/&lt;id&gt;.json</code> &mdash; per-file detail</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Talking points (for podcast / TV producers)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>"The Pentagon released 162 files. The most striking ones aren't the most famous ones."</li>
    <li>"There is no proof of aliens in this release. There is also no proof against."</li>
    <li>"Trained military personnel observed objects with kinematics no known craft can replicate. That's the actual story."</li>
    <li>"Every file is verifiable. Every score is reproducible. The methodology is open."</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Highest-anomaly files</h2>
  <ul>
    {% for f in high_anomaly[:10] %}
    <li><a href="files/{{ f.id }}.html">{{ f.title }}</a> &mdash; score {{ (f.score or {}).value }}</li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Press inquiries: <em>[fill in your contact email before deploy]</em></p>

</main>

<footer style="text-align:center;padding:60px 24px;color:#7a92b0;font-size:13px;border-top:1px solid rgba(82,180,255,.1);margin-top:60px">
  <p><a href="../index.html" style="color:#52b4ff">Back to index</a> · <a href="verdict.html" style="color:#52b4ff">The honest verdict</a> · <a href="top-10.html" style="color:#52b4ff">Top 10</a></p>
</footer>
</body>
</html>
